of the RBB if I were to win?   What's the generally accepted rule on this? <p><p><font face="Arial">Hawkline Monster<br>
Level 50 Paladin<br>
Deus ex Machina</font></p><br>
<p><img border="0" src="http://home1.gte.net/res0096m/images/nosensesig.gif" width="485" height="121"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhalarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Halarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/5/01 7:59:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> If you wanted to do the &quot;honorable&quot; thing you could throw the RBB right back into the raids loot for an immediate roll on it.  That way someone else gets some dragon haste and there's no unhappy people.  If you were asking with the intent of keeping both items for yourself I'd say that's a no-no, you're dragon hasted, let someone else be too.<br>
<br>
Halarus<br>
54 enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscalekvoxbait.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scalek Voxbait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/5/01 8:01:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> i would say dont roll on it unless everyone has dragon haste or better.....<br>
<br>
but, if you did want to, ask the raid leader and make sure it would be ok with everyone, and i would suggest saying that if you do win, that you would put your RBB up for random to the people on the raid that rolled on the CoF.....<br>
<br>
otherwise you might leave people with a very sour taste in their mouths (sp.)...<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Scalek
56th Iksar Monk of Watchers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhawkline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hawkline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>D-O-R-K</span><br>  Posts: 1674<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/5/01 11:43:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> My main question was if it was ok to roll, and then to be sure if it was going to be ok to the people from the raid i got the RBB on.  If I were to win, I would agree putting that back in to the present raiders roll would feel the most right.  thanks! <p><p><font face="Arial">Hawkline Monster<br>
Level 50 Paladin<br>
Deus ex Machina</font></p><br>
<p><img border="0" src="http://home1.gte.net/res0096m/images/nosensesig.gif" width="485" height="121"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1978<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/5/01 8:40:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=153 width=142></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> i'd just be in on the roll unless a majority of the raid helped you get the rbb. <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeyanaubaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyan Aubaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/6/01 7:48:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> yah what nillon said...<br>
<br>
CoF is an upgrade compared to RBB (35% instead of 30% if my memory isnt too F'd up), imo turning in the RBB would be a nice thing, but certainly not something you should feel forced to do.<br>
<br>
That's if you do plan on using the cloak over the belt of course <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 691<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/6/01 9:29:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> IMO the RBB should be turned over to the raid that you got it on. NOT the current raid you got the CoF on.  Those tanks that were on the raid where the RBB dropped are the ones that deserve to roll on it.  Same holds true with the CoF if you ever get better, it should be rolled among those on the raid that the CoF dropped.<br>
<br>
I always keep a screen shot of any rolls when I win something like that.  When I won the Staff of Forbidden Rights I took a screen shot of the names in the roll, same when I won a Naggy Bag.  That way if I need to roll it among those that were there I can pull up the screen shot and roll it among the names on the list.<br>
<br>
Just my 2pp.. <p>Jaradis Stormcaller - 51st Mystic
Guild Leader - Mystic Dominion<br>
Twiggie Tymberwolf - 52rd Retired Wanderer<br><br><i>People demand freedom of speech as a compensation for the freedom of thought  which they seldom use.</i> - Soren Kierkegaard</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 715<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/7/01 4:17:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://daydream-graphics.com/artists/hoover/qhorcishhealer.jpg width=112 height=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Dragon Loot Question</span><hr size=1> Roll on the cloak.  It's better than a RBB under normal circumstances<br>
<br>
One thing to keep in mind is that in the future, you may actually want to revert back to the RBB.<br>
Lodizal Shell Shield + RBB vs Cloak of Flames + ? belt.....tough call.<br>
Is 5% haste worth a sizable boost in AC, sizable boost in resists, more stats, and a huuuge boost in wis?<br>
If it comes to that, though, I'm sure you could easily trade a CoF to someone for a RBB. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>58 Halfling Shaman
<br><img src=http://www.tbp.mb.ca/~stimpy/everquest/JuujuuHalflingSentry.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1509.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1505.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.threadControl?topicID=1507.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1507.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1507.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilisfrm64">Archived Threads<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Races and Classes <option value="brellserilisroleplaying">Tome: History of Norrath<option value="br